3. Préparation de df (Fusion & Nettoyage)¶

In [17]:
# 3.1 Sélection de la couche surface des courants
currents_surf = currents.sel(depth=currents.depth.min())

# 3.2 Interpolation nearest sur la grille vent
curr2wind = currents_surf.sel(
    time=wind.valid_time,
    latitude=wind.latitude,
    longitude=wind.longitude,
    method='nearest'
)
bath2wind = bathymetry.sel(
    lat=wind.latitude,
    lon=wind.longitude,
    method='nearest'
)

# 3.3 Construction du Dataset xarray fusionné
ds = xr.Dataset({
    'u10':      (wind.u10.dims,      wind.u10.data),
    'v10':      (wind.v10.dims,      wind.v10.data),
    'u_curr':   (curr2wind.uo.dims,  curr2wind.uo.data),
    'v_curr':   (curr2wind.vo.dims,  curr2wind.vo.data),
    'elevation':(bath2wind.elevation.dims, bath2wind.elevation.data),
}, coords={
    'time':     wind.valid_time,
    'latitude': wind.latitude,
    'longitude':wind.longitude
})

# 3.4 Conversion en DataFrame et renommages
df = ds.to_dataframe().reset_index().rename(columns={'valid_time':'time'})
df = df.drop(columns=['number','expver'], errors='ignore')

# 3.5 Imputation des NaN (médiane)
for col in ['u_curr','v_curr','elevation']:
    df[col].fillna(df[col].median(), inplace=True)

print("df shape:", df.shape)

5. Prétraitement & Définition de la cible¶

In [19]:
# 5.1 Outliers: capping aux 1/99 percentiles sur u10, v10
for col in ['u10','v10']:
    low, high = df[col].quantile([0.01,0.99])
    df[col] = df[col].clip(low, high)

# 5.2 Target binaire (u10 > 75ᵉ percentile)
df['target'] = (df['u10'] > df['u10'].quantile(0.75)).astype(int)
print("Répartition target:\n", df['target'].value_counts())

# 5.3 (Option) SMOTE pour l'équilibre
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
X_sm = df[['v10','u_curr','v_curr','elevation']]
y_sm = df['target']
X_res, y_res = SMOTE(random_state=42).fit_resample(X_sm, y_sm)
print("Après SMOTE:\n", pd.Series(y_res).value_counts())

6. Réseau Bayésien¶

In [20]:
# 6.1 Discrétisation
disc_cols = ['u10','v10','u_curr','v_curr','elevation']
disc_df = df[disc_cols].copy()
for col in disc_cols:
    disc_df[col] = pd.cut(disc_df[col], bins=5, labels=False)

# 6.2 Structure learning
hc = HillClimbSearch(disc_df)
best_struct = hc.estimate(scoring_method=BicScore(disc_df))

# 6.3 Fit du modèle
bn = BayesianNetwork(best_struct.edges())
bn.fit(disc_df, estimator=BayesianEstimator, prior_type='BDeu')

print("Arêtes apprises :", bn.edges())

7. Clustering Ascendant Hiérarchique (CAH)¶

In [21]:
# 7.1 Normalisation
features = ['u10','v10','u_curr','v_curr','elevation']
X_scaled = StandardScaler().fit_transform(df[features])

# 7.2 Dendrogramme
Z = linkage(X_scaled, method='ward')
plt.figure()
dendrogram(Z, truncate_mode='level', p=5)
plt.title("Dendrogramme CAH")
plt.show()

# 7.3 Découpage en k clusters
k = 4
df['cluster'] = fcluster(Z, k, criterion='maxclust')
print("Répartition des clusters :\n", df['cluster'].value_counts())

# 7.4 Centres moyens
print("Centres moyens par cluster :")
print(df.groupby('cluster')[features].mean())

8. Arbre de Décision¶

In [23]:
# 8. Arbre de Décision
# 8.1 Entraînement
X_dt = df[['v10','u_curr','v_curr','elevation']]
y_dt = df['target']
dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=4, random_state=42)
dt.fit(X_dt, y_dt)

# 8.2 Prédictions & métriques
y_pred = dt.predict(X_dt)
print("Accuracy DT :", accuracy_score(y_dt, y_pred))
print(classification_report(y_dt, y_pred))

# 8.3 Matrice de confusion
cm = confusion_matrix(y_dt, y_pred)
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')
plt.title("Matrice de confusion – Arbre de décision")
plt.xlabel("Prédit")
plt.ylabel("Réel")
plt.show()

# 8.4 ROC & AUC
y_proba = dt.predict_proba(X_dt)[:,1]
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_dt, y_proba)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC = {roc_auc:.2f}")
plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'--')
plt.title("ROC Curve – Decision Tree")
plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# 8.5 Visualisation de l'arbre
plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
plot_tree(dt, feature_names=X_dt.columns, class_names=['0','1'], filled=True)
plt.show()

9. Deep Learning¶

In [24]:
# 9. Deep Learning

import tensorflow as tf
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# 9.1 Préparation des données
features_dl = ['v10','u_curr','v_curr','elevation']
X_dl = df[features_dl].values
y_dl = df['target'].values

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_dl, y_dl, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)

# 9.2 Définition du modèle
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(X_train.shape[1],)),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])

model.compile(
    optimizer='adam',
    loss='binary_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

# 9.3 Callbacks
callbacks = [
    tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(
        monitor='val_loss',
        patience=5,
        restore_best_weights=True
    ),
    tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(
        os.path.join(PROCESSED_DIR, 'best_model.keras'),
        monitor='val_accuracy',
        save_best_only=True
    )
]

# 9.4 Entraînement
history = model.fit(
    X_train, y_train,
    validation_split=0.2,
    epochs=50,
    batch_size=32,
    callbacks=callbacks,
    verbose=1
)

# 9.5 Évaluation
loss, acc = model.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
print(f"⚡️ Précision DL sur test : {acc:.3f}")

# 9.6 Courbes d'apprentissage
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))

# Loss
plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train loss')
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='val loss')
plt.title('Loss')
plt.xlabel('Époque')
plt.legend()

# Accuracy
plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='train acc')
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='val acc')
plt.title('Accuracy')

plt.legend()

# 10.1 Matrice de confusion & ROC pour le modèle DL
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, roc_curve, auc

# Prédiction binaire
y_pred_dl = (model.predict(X_test) > 0.5).astype(int)

# Matrice de confusion
cm_dl = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_dl)
plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))
sns.heatmap(cm_dl, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Purples')
plt.title("Matrice de confusion – Deep Learning")
plt.xlabel("Prédit")
plt.ylabel("Réel")
plt.show()

# ROC & AUC
y_proba_dl = model.predict(X_test).ravel()
fpr_dl, tpr_dl, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_proba_dl)
roc_auc_dl = auc(fpr_dl, tpr_dl)

plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))
plt.plot(fpr_dl, tpr_dl, label=f"AUC = {roc_auc_dl:.2f}")
plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'--', color='gray')
plt.title("ROC Curve – Deep Learning")
plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
plt.legend()
plt.show()
